elphia 76ers]]\n| {{sort|11|11}}\n| [[2013 NBA draft|2013]]\n|-\n| {{nbay|2014}}\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"background-color:#CFECEC;\"|{{sortname|Andrew|Wiggins}}^\n| [[Forward (basketball)|Forward]]/[[Guard (basketball)|Guard]]\n| {{CAN}}\n| [[Minnesota Timberwolves]]\n| {{sort|01|[[List of first overall NBA draft picks|1]]}}\n| [[2014 NBA draft|2014]]\n|-\n|{{nbay|2015}}\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"background-color:#CFECEC;\"|{{sortname|Karl-Anthony|Towns}}^{{dagger}}\n| [[Center (basketball)|Center]]\n| {{flagu|Dominican Republic}}{{#tag:ref|Karl-Anthony Towns was born and raised in the United States to an American father and a Dominican mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.startribune.com/karl-anthony-towns-drafted-no-1-overall-by-timberwolves-as-expected/309936841/|title=Karl-Anthony Towns taken No.1 by Wolves; Tyus Jones acquired in trade with Cavaliers|first=Jerry|last=Zgoda|date=June 26, 2015|publisher=Star Tribune|accessdate=June 26, 2015}}</ref> He has represented the [[Dominican Republic national basketball team|Dominican Republic]] internationally since 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wkyt.com/sports/headlines/Calipari_makes_Dominican_team_roster_cuts_159306055.html?ref=055|title=Calipari makes Dominican team roster cuts|date=June 16, 2012|publisher=WKYT|accessdate=June 26, 2015}}</ref>|group=lower-alpha}}\n| [[Minnesota Timberwolves]]\n| {{sort|01|[[List of first overall NBA draft picks|1]]}}\n| [[2015 NBA draft|2015]]\n|-\n|{{nbay|2016}}\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"background-color:#CFECEC;\"|{{sortname|Malcolm|Brogdon}}^\n| [[Guard (basketball)|Guard]]\n| {{flagu|United States}}\n| [[Milwaukee Bucks]]\n| {{sort|36|36}}\n| [[2016 NBA draft|2016]]\n|-\n|{{nbay|2017}}\n!scope=\"row\" style=\"background-color:#CFECEC;\"|{{sortname|Ben|Simmons}}^\n| [[Forward (basketball)|Forward]]/[[Guard (basketball)|Guard]]\n| {{AUS}}\n| [[Philadelphia 76ers]]\n| {{sort|01|[[List of first overall NBA draft picks|1]]}}\n| [[2016 NBA draft|2016]]{{#tag:ref|Though drafted in 20